{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-00046/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-00046"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:00:46"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["low key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman sitting in an armchair by a fire speaks to someone offscreen."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00046/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-00046","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00046/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-00046"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00046/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00046/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00046/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00046/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00046/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00046/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00046/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00046/canvas/1/556e4ae0-0595-4966-bd0b-b06aeaa59477","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T13:36:03.461Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The first character we see is Alma, and her close-up encourages intimacy and identification. The warm light that envelopes her combined with her assertion that Reynolds has made all her dreams come true establishes Alma as a docile, soft-spoken character who bows to the main character's power. The first word she utters is “Reynolds,” which only confirms this suggestion. This dynamic holds true for most of the film, at least until a plot point undoes and turns power hierarchies on their head.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00046/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:471.89127105666154,47.1362940275651,1242.2434915773354,1002.5650842266461"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00046/canvas/1/9cc1a935-7ab0-4999-8109-3b90127ce7cb","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T13:36:16.344Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The film’s opening, with Alma’s confession that she has given Reynolds “every piece” of her, is clearly interested in setting up certain expectations that will be subverted by the end. Audiences will anticipate a story of her submission as a woman in this relationship, when, in fact, they adopt a much more complex dynamic between themselves. Likewise, she is the one providing an interpretative lens to their relationship, not Reynolds, granting her agency and control over the story.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00046/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:19.49081163859116,54.3376722817764,231.62710566615615,164.47166921898915"}}}]}]}]}